# ORION CTL Âµ-ROS Libraries

Welcome to the libraries for the ORION actuators

## Content

Here you can find the next elements:

- **[constants](/orion_base/orion_ctl_micro_ros/lib/constants/constants.hpp):** Related with PID and PWM values for constants.
- **[encoder](/orion_base/orion_ctl_micro_ros/lib/encoder/):** Oriented to create encoder objects to use two-channel encoders of DC motors to get speed and direction.
- **[hardware](/orion_base/orion_ctl_micro_ros/lib/hardware/hardware.hpp):** Related with the ports value of the actuators.
- **[motor](/orion_base/orion_ctl_micro_ros/lib/motor/):** For using a DC Motor with a L298N driver having access to control the direction and the speed of the motor.
- **[pid](/orion_base/orion_ctl_micro_ros/lib/pid/):** Controller implementation to compute the motor movement.
- **[servo](/orion_base/orion_ctl_micro_ros/lib/servo/):** For using a ServoMotor, in this case, a MG996r to set/get the motor position on rad and degrees.

## PlatfomIO Library Structure

This directory is intended for project specific (private) libraries.
PlatformIO will compile them to static libraries and link into the executable file.

The source code of each library should be placed in a separate directory
("lib/your_library_name/[Code]").

For example, see the structure of the following example libraries `Foo` and `Bar`:

|--lib
|  |
|  |--Bar
|  |  |--docs
|  |  |--examples
|  |  |--src
|  |     |- Bar.c
|  |     |- Bar.h
|  |  |- library.json (optional. for custom build options, etc) More info on [LibraryManager](https://docs.platformio.org/page/librarymanager/config.html)
|  |
|  |--Foo
|  |  |- Foo.c
|  |  |- Foo.h
|  |
|  |- README --> THIS FILE
|
|- platformio.ini
|--src
   |- main.c

Example contents of `src/main.c` using Foo and Bar:

```C
#include <Foo.h>
#include <Bar.h>

int main (void)
{
  ...
}

```

The PlatformIO Library Dependency Finder will find automatically dependent
libraries by scanning project source files.

More information about PlatformIO Library Dependency Finder:

- [LibraryManager](https://docs.platformio.org/page/librarymanager/config.html)
